Microsoft announces Xbox figures, confirms Japan, Europe, Australia debuts 
Microsoft said announced Tuesday it has sold 1.5 million units of its
Xbox video game since its November 15 launch.
The company also said it was on track to debut the device in Japan on
February 22, with European and Australian Xbox launches on March 14.
The announcements came at the International Consumer Electronics Show
behind held this week in Las Vegas.
The company also released figures from technology consultancy NPD
Group, which said gamers were buying three games for every Xbox sold,
the highest such radio for a new video game console.
Microsoft's Xbox is a new entry into the fiercely competitive
multi-billion dollar home video gaming market, so far dominated by
Nintendo and Sony.
